-integrated context retrieval over a corpus of Vietnamese legal documents in the domain of fees and taxation. The proposed pipeline consists of document collection, hierarchical graph construction with explicit cross-document references, and the generation of a tailored question–answer benchmark dataset for graph-vector retrieval comparison. We evaluate multiple retrieval strategies by comparing graph-based retrieval methods with traditional vector-based similarity retrieval to evaluate our hypothesis regarding the effectiveness of graph-integrated retrieval in the Legal document system.  \\nExperimental results indicate that while the proposed graph-based approach does not yet consistently outperform vector retrieval in all settings, it provides improved interpretability, citation traceability, and document structural awareness. These findings highlight the potential of graph representations to address fundamental limitations of traditional legal RAG systems and suggest directions for future improvements.  \\n3  \\nGroup Project  \\nTax Legal Retrieval with Graph Representation Assistant  \\nGroup 55', metadata={'header_2': '**Abstract**'}), embedding=[-0.005016326904296875, 0.035675048828125, 0.0196533203125, -0.00433349609375, -0.0186920166015625, -0.009521484375, -0.025665283203125, -0.00762176513671875, -0.012359619140625, -0.002567291259765625, -0.00307464599609375, -0.04754638671875, 0.00257110595703125, -0.0232696533203125, 0.020233154296875, 0.0033321380615234375, 0.020965576171875, -0.0282440185546875, -0.008331298828125, 0.01806640625, 0.037811279296875, -0.00452423095703125, 0.03997802734375, 0.00213623046875, -0.0164642333984375, -0.05255126953125, 0.034088134765625, 0.01435089111328125, 0.024169921875, -0.0189971923828125, 0.007404327392578125, -0.029815673828125, -0.0246124267578125, -0.007556915283203125, -0.01059722900390625, 0.07940673828125, -0.007167816162109375, -0.01050567626953125, 0.004627227783203125, 0.01340484619140625, 0.0188140869140625,