tChunk(header=<MarkdownHeader.H2: '##'>, header_type=<MarkdownHeader.H2: '##'>, header_name='metadata extraction', content='To capture the Document’s information such as **Document Type, Issued Location** or **Issue Date** , a model was built revolving around the Named Entity Recognition (NER) algorithm. Although extensive research has been conducted on NER for either legal documents or Vietnamese text, identifying a specific research direction that intersects these two domains to align with our initial scope remains a challenge. Without any officially available dataset, we created our own annotated dataset by taking a sample of 80 Legal documents of different types (Law, Decrees, Circulars,..), extracted the first and the last sentence (containing the related information) and manually annotated the sentences using the self-defined labels on the locally-hosted Label-studio application.  \\nThe Labeling process follows the predefined patterns, due to our greater emphasis on detecting the Document’s ID and Date attributes, some document titles containing the ID and Date such as ” **Nghịđịnh Sửa đổi bổsung Nghịđịnh số23/BI/NĐ-CP ngày 1 tháng 2 năm 2025 vềvấn đề....** ” were labeled in a fragmented manner, which caused the model to miss the document title in certain cases.  \\n|**Information Type**|**Sample Value**|**Label**|\\n|---|---|---|\\n|Title|Luật Thu nhậpdoanh nghiệp|TIT|\\n|Document_ID|23BI/12/NĐ-CP|DOCID|\\n|Document_Type|Luật|TYP|\\n|Issuer Department|Chính Phủ|DEP|\\n|Issuer_Date|ngày13 tháng6 năm 2020|DAT|\\n|Issuer_Location|Hà Nội|LOC|\\n|Issuer|Phạm Minh Chính|PER|  \\n**Table 3:** NER labeling strategy  \\nFollowing the work from [15], we formulated a Single forward model architecture with an input embedding layer followed by 2 **Bidirectional LSTM** layers for fully capturing the semantic meaning of the input sentence. Following that a Feed-Forward layer with Pre Layer-Normalization and Attention mask are applied and feed the final result through a last **Conditional Random Field** designed for the sequence tagging tasks.  \\n13  \\nGroup Project  \\nTax Legal Retrieval with Graph Representation Assistant  \\nGroup 55  \\n**==> picture [317 x 237] intentionally omitted <==**  \\n**Figure 4:** Document Metadata Extraction Model  \\nThe Model prediction was returned in the form of BIO (Begin - Inner - Outer) tagging scheme, which follows the rule:  \\n```\\nActual:\"Ngay13thang6nam2025\"(DAT)\\nPrediction:\\n-\\nNgay(B-DAT)\\n-13(I-DAT)\\n-\\nthang(I-DAT)\\n-6(I-DAT)\\n-nam(I-DAT)\\n-2025(I-DAT)\\n-.(O)\\n```  \\nWe applied a set of post-processing steps to merge characters of the same type into a single block and enforced strict rules to prevent issues such as word fragmentation or case inconsistency. The resulting information was then automatically added as attributes of the central document node at the beginning of the processing phase.  \\n|**department**|**issue_date**|**title**|**location**|**document_id**|**issuer**|**document_type**|\\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\\n|Chính Phủ|13/07/2020|Nghịđịnh thayđổi…|Hà Nội|23/2020/NĐ-CP|Phạm Minh Chính|NghịĐịnh|  \\n**Table 4:** Sample Document Metadata Extraction', metadata={'header_2': '**Metadata Extraction**'}), embedding=[0.01049041748046875, 0.04241943359375, -0.010345458984375, -0.045928955078125, -0.0010623931884765625, 3.6776065826416016e-05, -0.0005283355712890625, 0.0008592605590820312, -0.055328369140625, -0.011871337890625, -0.00836944580078125, -0.0113525390625, -0.0419921875, -0.0528564453125, 0.006439208984375, 0.039276123046875, 0.0157470703125, 0.00881195068359375, 0.0019207000732421875, 0.0187225341796875, 0.056304931640625, 0.03192138671875, 0.03997802734375, -0.00482940673828125, 0.0310821533203125, -0.0274658203125, -0.01290130615234375, 0.0287933349609375, 0.02655029296875, -0.0140533447265625, -0.00838470458984375, -0.0217742919921875, 0.0305328369140625, -0.0021305084228515625, 0.00013780593872070312, 0.060211181640625, -0.001117706298828125,