 began the first stage by utilizing several chunking strategies adapted from traditional vector retrieval frameworks. These strategies are applied uniformly across general document structures without explicitly accounting for document-specific formatting. The Docling _HybridChunker_ performs structureaware segmentation by preserving coherent blocks or paragraphs within a single chunk and avoiding mid-paragraph splits, while maintaining a consistent target chunk size. As a result, it produces chunks of varying lengths, each composed of smaller hierarchical components.  \\nIn contrast, the _RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter_ from the **LangChain** pipeline aims to preserve semantic coherence by recursively splitting text using an ordered list of separators, typically paragraph breaks and newline characters. While this method largely preserves paragraphs and sentences, it focuses primarily on individual escape characters without explicit awareness of hierarchical structure.  \\nIn addition to the chunking strategies provided by existing frameworks, we also experimented with a _Fixed-SizeChunking_ strategy. In this approach, the document text is treated as a linear sequence of words-characters and segmented into fixed-length blocks of N words (with N=200 in our experiments), without overlap between chunks. This method completely ignores document structure and focuses solely on the textual content, serving as a random baseline for the experiment.', metadata={'header_2': '**Chunking Strategy**'}), embedding=[0.011749267578125, 0.037933349609375, 0.05877685546875, -0.01224517822265625, -0.0105133056640625, -0.0255126953125, 0.0211181640625, 0.037933349609375, -0.033447265625, 0.05029296875, 0.0294647216796875, -0.013458251953125, -0.07135009765625, 0.02239990234375, 0.0164031982421875, 0.020538330078125, 0.049072265625, -0.01026153564453125, -0.0316162109375, 0.042083740234375, 0.0330810546875, -0.020050048828125, -0.009735107421875, 0.0137939453125, 0.02130126953125, -0.0318