ctor _hx_ , the algorithm first applies neighborhood aggregation of feature vector, which is by aggregating the current node’s feature with its neighbors’ features, this aggregation function can either be a Mean, Max Pooling or even a small Long-Short Term Memory (LSTM) layer.  \\n**==> picture [229 x 20] intentionally omitted <==**  \\nThe aggregated hidden representation is then concatenated with the node’s original feature matrix and passes through a sigmoid-normalized linear layer to get the output hidden state of the current layer.  \\n**==> picture [205 x 21] intentionally omitted <==**  \\nTo mitigate the high computational cost of the algorithm and to ensure fault tolerance, we sampled a subset of the full document corpus and evaluated the graph embedding approach in conjunction with the custom chunking strategy described above. For the input data, we directly used textual node embeddings as inputs to the algorithms with the view to enriching these contextual embedding with positional features. To address the absence of textual content at the document’s central node, we incorporated two of its attributes— **document_type** and **amend** —thereby utilizing general document characteristics to enrich the graph embedding representation while still preserving the graph consistent structure.  \\n30  \\nGroup Project  \\nTax Legal Retrieval with Graph Representation Assistant  \\nGroup 55  \\nFor the GraphSAGE model training, we input directly input three of the node’s feature as input, the resulting embedding is the embedded combination of both node’s textual and positional representation.  \\n- **original_embedding** : The textual embedding derived from the node’s associated text using the embedding model. For nodes that do not contain explicit textual content, such as central nodes, the corresponding embeddings are initialized to zero vectors.  \\n- **document_type** : The document type is encoded using a predefined mapping dictionary and is available only at the central node. For all other nodes, the document_type attribute is set to zero.  \\n- **amend** : Whether a document is an amending document is represented as a binary flag (0/1) at the central node. For all other nodes, this attribute is set to −1.  \\n**==> picture [385 x 177] intentionally omitted <==**  \\n**----- Start of picture text -----**<br>\\nCentral Node<br>text = None<br>original_embedding = [0] Central Node<br>document_type<br>amend original_embedding = [0]<br>new_embedding = [ ]<br>Relational<br>Edges<br>GraphSAGE<br>Document Node<br>Document Node<br>original_embedding = [ ]<br>text  new_embedding = [ ]<br>original_embedding = Embedder(text)<br>document_type = 0<br>amend = -1<br>**----- End of picture text -----**<br>  \\n**Figure 14:** GraphSAGE pipeline', metadata={'header_2': '**GraphSAGE**'}), embedding=[-0.0020580291748046875, 0.035858154296875, 0.040771484375, -0.0252227783203125, -0.00583648681640625, -0.002506256103515625, 0.01092529296875, -0.024017333984375, -0.0379638671875, 0.0176239013671875, 0.0501708984375, -0.06964111328125, -0.034912109375, -0.03033447265625, 0.023712158203125, 0.01131439208984375, 0.0162506103515625, 0.0270843505859375, -0.01557159423828125, 0.039215087890625, 0.033660888671875, 0.013153076171875, 0.005767822265625, 0.005863189697265625, 0.004581451416015625, -0.020538330078125, 0.05572509765625, 0.055877685546875, 0.03424072265625, 0.004627227783203125, -0.0228271484375, -0.037017822265625, -0.006641387939453125, -0.0126190185546875, -0.0345458984375, 0.0394287109375, -0.049041748046875, 0.034942626953125, -0.02276611328125, 0.0204925537109375, 0.006763458251953125, -0.0130462646484375, -0.0098876953125, 0.042633056640625, -0.00780487060546875, 0.02093505859375, -0.016937255859375, -0.0015687942504882812, 0.0058746337890625, 0.027374267578125, -0.032745361328125, -0.0079345703125, -0.0159759521484375, 0.01485443115234375, 0.00032329559326171875, 0.024505615234375, -0.0255126953125, 0.00791168212890625, 0.0083084106