id='41', chunk=CompaktChunk(header=<MarkdownHeader.H2: '##'>, header_type=<MarkdownHeader.H2: '##'>, header_name='complex', content='The **ComplEx** embedding algorithm introduced and employed in researches like [29], despite less widely adopted than GraphSAGE or traditional graph embedding methods such as GCN or GIN, has demonstrated effectiveness in encoding graph relational structures into node embedding vectors by operating on triplet data of the form (source, edge_label, target) and projecting each entity and relation into a Complex vector space.  \\n**==> picture [163 x 13] intentionally omitted <==**  \\nFor a triplet (s,r,o) representing (source-relation-object) of a node relation, the algorithm applies a complex scoring function utilizing the Tri-linear dot-product utilizing both the Real and the Imaginary components of the representation.  \\n**==> picture [350 x 15] intentionally omitted <==**  \\nWhere the tri-linear dot-product can be expressed as:  \\n**==> picture [96 x 33] intentionally omitted <==**  \\nThe result is then used to calculate the updated model parameter using the learning rate _η_ and negative loss function with negative sampling (denoted by binary flag y).  \\n**==> picture [102 x 24] intentionally omitted <==**  \\n31  \\nGroup Project  \\nTax Legal Retrieval with Graph Representation Assistant  \\nGroup 55  \\nWhere  \\n**==> picture [163 x 27] intentionally omitted <==**  \\nThe resulting embedding from ComplEx is a k-dimensional vector in which each dimension is represented as a complex number composed of both real and imaginary components. To maintain the compatibility with standard vector similarity computations, the real and imaginary components of each dimension are flattened, yielding a new vector of dimension 2k.', metadata={'header_2': '**ComplEx**'}), embedding=[0.00971221923828125, 0.0155181884765625, 0.020416259765625, -0.01409149169921875, 0.03289794921875, -0.01172637939453125, 0.042724609375, -0.0196380615234375, -0.0