      "text/plain": [
       "[CompaktChunk(header=<MarkdownHeader.H2: '##'>, header_type=<MarkdownHeader.H2: '##'>, header_name='university of science and technology of hanoi department of information and communication technology', content='**==> picture [317 x 167] intentionally omitted <==**', metadata={'header_2': '**University of Science and Technology of Hanoi DEPARTMENT OF INFORMATION AND COMMUNICATION TECHNOLOGY**'}),\n",
       " CompaktChunk(header=<MarkdownHeader.H2: '##'>, header_type=<MarkdownHeader.H2: '##'>, header_name='group project report', content='**Tax Legal Retrieval with Graph Representation Assistant [** **`EN` ]**  \\n**Authors:**  \\nPham Duy Anh Nguyen Thai Nhat Anh Le Quoc Anh Dinh Thanh Hieu Ngo Xuan Kien Nguyen The Khai **Supervisor** : Tran Giang Son – ICT Department  \\n```\\n-\\nID23BI14023\\n-\\nID23BI14024\\n-\\nID23BI14025\\n-\\nID22BA13132\\n-\\nID23BI14239\\n-\\nID23BI14205\\n```  \\nHANOI, 2025  \\nTax Legal Retrieval with Graph Representation Assistant  \\nGroup 55', metadata={'header_2': '**Group Project Report**'}),\n",
       " CompaktChunk(header=<MarkdownHeader.H2: '##'>, header_type=<MarkdownHeader.H2: '##'>, header_name='acknowledgement', content='This project was strongly influenced and supported by Professor Tran Giang Son, the Director of Department of Information and Communication Technology, University of Science and Technology of Hanoi (ICT-USTH). We would like to express our sincere gratitude for his thoughtful guidance, valuable recommendations, and continuous support throughout the course of this project. Without his sustained involvement and encouragement, this work would not have been completed to its present extent.  \\n2  \\nGroup Project  \\nTax Legal Retrieval with Graph Representation Assistant  \\nGroup 55', metadata={'header_2': '**Acknowledgement**'}),\n",
       " CompaktChunk(header=<MarkdownHeader.H2: '##'>, header_type=<MarkdownHeader.H2: '##'>, header_name='abstract', content='Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) has become a popular, widely-applied approach for grounding Large Language Models (LLM) with external knowledge. However, traditional RAG systems primarily rely on flat, stateless text chunking without hierarchical awareness, which struggles to capture the semantic structure and dense cross-referencing network in legal documents, especially Vietnamese official legal documents.  \\nIn this work, we propose a comprehensive end-to-end framework for graph-integrated context retrieval over a corpus of Vietnamese legal documents in the domain of fees and taxation. The proposed pipeline consists of document collection, hierarchical graph construction with explicit cross-document references, and the generation of a tailored question–answer benchmark dataset for graph-vector retrieval comparison. We evaluate multiple retrieval strategies by comparing graph-based retrieval methods with traditional vector-based similarity retrieval to evaluate our hypothesis regarding the effectiveness of graph-integrated retrieval in the Legal document system.  \\nExperimental results indicate that while the proposed graph-based approach does not yet consistently outperform vector retrieval in all settings, it provides improved interpretability, citation traceability, and document structural awareness. These findings highlight the potential of graph representations to address fundamental limitations of traditional legal RAG systems and suggest directions for future improvements.  \\n3  \\nGroup Project  \\nTax Legal Retrieval with Graph Representation Assistant  \\nGroup 55', metadata={'header_2': '**Abstract**'}),\n",
